# American English Spelling

## ZERO DISCRETION POLICY

All text in this codebase — user-facing copy, code comments, docstrings, variable
names, string literals, template content, and commit messages — must use American
English spelling. No exceptions.

Prohibited judgement calls:
- "Colour is the correct international spelling." — No. Use `color`.
- "Behaviour is standard in many style guides." — No. Use `behavior`.
- "This is a direct quote from a government form." — No. Normalize to American English in our code and copy.

---

## Common substitutions

| British | American |
|---|---|
| colour | color |
| behaviour / behavioural | behavior / behavioral |
| centre / centred | center / centered |
| honour / honoured | honor / honored |
| organisation / organised | organization / organized |
| recognise / recognised | recognize / recognized |
| analyse / analysed | analyze / analyzed |
| licence (noun) | license |
| defence | defense |
| programme | program |
| travelling | traveling |
| cancelled | canceled |
| labelling | labeling |
| fulfil / fulfilment | fulfill / fulfillment |
| grey | gray |
| cheque | check |
| prioritise | prioritize |
| initialise | initialize |
| serialise | serialize |
| normalise | normalize |

---

## Scope

This rule applies to:
- Jinja2 template text and comments
- Python docstrings and inline comments
- Python string literals (error messages, log messages, UI copy)
- Variable and function names (e.g. `normalize_` not `normalise_`)
- Commit messages
- ADR documents and any `.md` files in this repo

## Typography

Em-dashes (`—`, U+2014) and en-dashes (`–`, U+2013) are prohibited everywhere
in this codebase — in the same way emoji are prohibited. Use a plain hyphen-minus
(`-`) in CLI output, code comments, and string literals. Use a spaced hyphen
(` - `) where a dash is needed for readability.

This applies to:
- CLI output strings (`click.echo`, `print`)
- Python docstrings, comments, log messages, error messages
- Template text and any user-facing copy
- Commit messages and documentation files

